  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230ºC/ 210ºC (fan)/ gas 8</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Cut your<strong> waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into thick rings</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut a piece (or two!) of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or <strong>tin foil</strong>) approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>onion rings</strong> and <strong>garlic clove[s] </strong>(skin on) in the middle of the baking paper piece[s], then transfer to a baking tray[s]</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cut a knob of <strong>butter</strong> into small cubes and dot them all over the potatoes</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the baking paper together around the potatoes to form a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Put the baking tray[s] in the oven for 40 min or until the potatoes are golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are in the oven, separate the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> from the <strong>white[s]</strong> by cracking your <strong>egg[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>over a small bowl and catching the yolk in the shell</p><p>Transfer the yolk from one shell half to the other several times, until all the whites are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell, then add the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Tip: Hold on to those egg whites! They’re perfect for meringues or a protein-rich omelette (they freeze well too)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
