    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat then add your <strong>crème fraîche</strong> and your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>egg yolk[s]</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further, stirring constantly, or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Stir through the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your<strong> béarnaise sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-5-x200.jpg",
