            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have been in for 25 min, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>sirloin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, drizzle with<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides and once very hot, add the<strong> steak</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side then once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2441tep-6-x200.jpg",
