            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to wilt, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>béarnaise sauce</strong> to a very low heat and cook for 1 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
